<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>How It Works - ProduceBridge</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 100px;
            background-image: url(<%= asset_path 'loginbackground.jpg' %>);
            background-size: cover;
            background-position: center;
            background-repeat: no-repeat;
            background-attachment: fixed; /* Keeps the background fixed when scrolling */
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 50px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9); /* Adds a slight transparency to container */
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            border-radius: 8px;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #2b8a3e;
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 40px;
        }
        h2 {
            color: #2b8a3e;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
        p {
            font-size: 18px;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #333;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        .step {
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }
        .footer {
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 40px;
            font-size: 14px;
            color: #777;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="container">
        <h1>How It Works</h1>

        <div class="step">
            <h2>Step 1: Sign Up</h2>
            <p>Join our platform by creating an account. Whether you're a truck driver, grocery store, farm, or nonprofit organization, it’s quick and easy.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
            <h2>Step 2: List Your Surplus</h2>
            <p>If you have excess food items—be it fresh produce, canned goods, or other perishable products—simply list them on our platform. You can include details about the items, quantities, and pick-up or delivery options.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
            <h2>Step 3: Connect with Local Needs</h2>
            <p>Connect with others in the area, from local food pantries, farmers with livestock, and other organizations that could benefit from your surplus. You can also set alerts for specific items or needs that interest you.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
            <h2>Step 4: Arrange Transfer</h2>
            <p>Once you find a match, coordinate with the receiving organization for pick-up or delivery. ProduceBridge provides tools to make the logistics as seamless as possible, ensuring that food reaches those who need it most.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
            <h2>Step 5: Make a Difference</h2>
            <p>By participating, you’re not only helping to feed those in need but also contributing to a more sustainable food system. Together, we can create a healthier community while reducing waste.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="footer">
            &copy; 2024 ProduceBridge. All rights reserved.
        </div>
    </div>

</body>
</html>
